benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client

Class GetCrimeDataTask<CrimeResultData extends UtvarAndIntervalBasedCrimeSummary>

  • java.lang.Object
      • benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client.RetainedAsyncTask<CrimeResultData>
        • benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client.GetCrimeDataTask<CrimeResultData>
  • Type Parameters:
    CrimeResultData - the result data type parameter
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GetCrimeDetailAsyncTask, GetCrimeListAsyncTask, GetCrimeSummaryAsyncTask, GetUtvarDetailAsyncTask

    public abstract class GetCrimeDataTask<CrimeResultData extends UtvarAndIntervalBasedCrimeSummary>
extends RetainedAsyncTask<CrimeResultData>
    GetCrimeDataTask is an abstract base class for the async tasks loading the crime data.

    This is a subclass of RetainedAsyncTask specialized on retrieving the CrimeResultData. CrimeResultData extends UtvarAndIntervalBasedCrimeSummary, the base interface for all the crime data.

    To retrieve the crime data, a certain method of CrimeMonitor service is called. This class stores the parameters used to make the call. Those are

    • the service base URL
    • the crime data interval
    • the department code

      Those parameters are combined into a so called CrimeService method call URL ("method call URL" from now on). The method call URL conforms to the defined URL notation used for the CrimeMonitor service method calls. Please consult the CrimeMonitor service documentation to get the detailed information about the method calling notation.

    Author:
    Tom
